headline: Morgan Stanley: Tariffs to hit new vehicle prices hardest, auto parts resilient
summary: Investing.com -- Tariffs on imported goods are likely to weigh most heavily on new vehicle prices, while aftermarket auto parts and home improvement products may prove more resilient, Morgan Stanley said.
